The paper deals with streaming algorithms and approximation algorithms for clustering sparse big data, which are topics that fall under the categories of data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), data mining (cs.DM), databases (cs.DB), and information theory (cs.IT). The paper's focus on clustering and approximation algorithms makes cs.DS and cs.LG the most likely categories, followed by cs.DM and cs.DB, which are also relevant to the paper's content. The paper's use of information theory concepts, such as coresets, makes cs.IT a possible category as well.
